conclusion: Objects A and B are moving through the air and are placed down at the location of objects C, D, E, and F.
Due to gravity, objects A and B will come into contact with objects C, D, E, and F.
Objects A and B will exert a force on objects C, D, E, and F.
The force exerted by objects A and B will be greater than the force of gravity holding objects C, D, E, and F on the table.
Objects C, D, E, and F will be pushed off the table by the force exerted by objects A and B.
